{
  "id": "dummy",
  "name": "Dummy Deck",
  "description": "Sandbox for testing new technical phrases before migration.",
  "deckType": "flippable",
  "cards": [
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_018",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Al recibir la alerta, revisé los registros.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "Upon receiving the alert, I checked the logs.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_018_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "On receiving the alert, I reviewed the logs.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_018_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Upon getting the alert, I checked the logs.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_018_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "**[164]**\n\n\n\n~When I recibied the alert, I checked the logs.~ is invalid due to a spelling mistake. The correct past tense is [received].\n\n~By receiving the alert, I checked the logs.~ is not grammatically logical in this context. The preposition [by] indicates the method used to achieve a result, but you don't check logs *by means of* receiving an alert. You check them *immediately after* the alert, which requires [upon] or [on]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_020",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Lo que quiero configurar es que esto haga eso.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "What I want to set up is for this to do that.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_020_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "What I want to configure is for this to do that.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_020_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "What I am trying to set up is for it to do that.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_020_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "**[194]**\n\n~What I want to set up is this to do that~ and ~What I want to set up is to do that~ are not valid. When expressing that you want an object or system to perform an action, you must use the structure [for] + [object] + [to do]. The correct form is [for this to do that]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_025",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Si, el esta a mi lado.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "Yes, he's next to me.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_025_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Yes, he is right beside me.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_025_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Yes, he's by my side.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_025_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Yes, he's at my side.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_025_sideB_3.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "**[217]**"
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_027",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Tienes permitido traducir esto de español a inglés y viceversa.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "You are allowed to translate this from Spanish to English and vice versa.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_027_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "You are permitted to translate this from Spanish to English and vice versa.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_027_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "You can translate this from Spanish to English and vice versa.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_027_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "\n\n~You have allow to translate this from Spanish to English and vice versa~ is not valid because 'allow' is a verb, not a noun. You must use [You are allowed to] or [You have permission to]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_028",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Estaba desactualizado ese codigo.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "That code was outdated.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_028_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "That code was deprecated.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_028_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "That code was out of date.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_028_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "\n\n~That code was outdateded~ is not valid because the word [outdated] is already an adjective. It does not take an extra '-ed' ending."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_029",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "En la mañana actualice el codigo.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "I updated the code this morning.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_029_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I pushed the code update this morning.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_029_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I refreshed the code in the morning.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_029_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I updated the code in the morning.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_029_sideB_3.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_030",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Perdona, se me pego (congelo) el programa.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "Sorry, my program froze.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_030_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "My apologies, the program crashed on me.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_030_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Sorry, the program got stuck.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_030_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Sorry, the program got frozen.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_030_sideB_3.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "**[218]**\n\n\n\n~Sorry, the program got froze~ and ~Sorry, the program got freeze~ are not valid because the past participle of 'freeze' is [frozen]. You can say it [got frozen], but it is much more natural to just say it [froze]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_033",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Gracias por ser paciente conmigo.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "Thank you for being patient with me.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_033_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Thanks for your patience.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_033_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I appreciate your patience with me.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_033_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Thanks for being patient with me.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_033_sideB_3.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_036",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Él se sentó a mi lado en la reunión.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "He sat next to me in the meeting.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_036_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "He sat beside me in the meeting.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_036_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "He sat right next to me at the meeting.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_036_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "He sat by me in the meeting.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_036_sideB_3.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "He sat by my side in the meeting.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_036_sideB_4.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "**[217]**\n\n[Next to] and [beside] indicate being directly adjacent. ~Beside to me~ is incorrect."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_037",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Quiero un escritorio junto a la ventana.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "I want a desk by the window.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_037_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I'd like a desk by the window.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_037_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I want a desk right by the window.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_037_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I want a desk next to the window.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_037_sideB_3.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I want a desk near the window.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_037_sideB_4.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "**[217]**\n\nUsing [by] is very natural to describe being right next to a window, a door, or a body of water.\n\n~I want a desktop by the window~ is not valid because 'desktop' refers to a type of computer or a digital screen interface. The physical furniture you sit at is called a [desk]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_038",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Lo acabo de pegar en el chat.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "I just pasted it in the chat.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_038_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I just dropped it in the chat.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_038_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I've just pasted it into the chat.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_038_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_039",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Necesito la confirmacion de lo que pedi",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "I need confirmation of what I requested.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_039_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I need the confirmation for my request.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_039_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I need confirmation on what I asked for.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_039_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I need the confirmation of what I requested.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_039_sideB_3.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "\n\n~what I asked~ implies you need confirmation of a question you asked, not a request. Use [what I asked for]. Also, ~confirm of~ is grammatically invalid because 'confirm' is a direct verb and does not use 'of'. Use [need to confirm what I requested]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_040",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "¿Necesitan algo mas?, 'No por mi lado.'",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "Do you need anything else? 'Not on my end.'",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_040_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Do you guys need anything else? 'Nothing on my side.'",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_040_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Is there anything else you need? 'Not from my side.'",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_040_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Do you need anything else? 'No, I'm good.'",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_040_sideB_3.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "**[202]**\n\n~Nothing by my side~ means something is physically missing next to you. To mean 'from my perspective or team', use [on my side] or [on my end].\n\n~No on my end~ is not grammatically natural. You should use [Not on my end] or [Nothing on my end]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_041",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Cree eso hace un largo tiempo atras, debo checkearlo",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "I created that a long time ago, I need to check it.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_041_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I set that up a while ago, I should look into it.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_041_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I made that a long time ago, I need to look it over.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_041_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_042",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Ha sido un largo tiempo poniendonos al dia en la arquitectura",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "It's taken a long time to get up to speed on the architecture.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_042_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "We've spent a long time catching up on the architecture.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_042_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "It took a long time to get caught up with the architecture.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_042_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "It has been a long time catching up on the architecture.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_042_sideB_3.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_043",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "…Y ellos hacen su trabajo optimizando los binarios para generar las APPs finales.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "...And they do their job optimizing the binaries to generate the final apps.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_043_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "...And they do their work optimizing the binaries to build the final apps.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_043_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "...And they handle the optimization of the binaries to output the final apps.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_043_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "And they work optimizing the binaries to output the final apps.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_043_sideB_3.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_044",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Los emails estan llegando al workflow test folder.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "The emails are arriving in the workflow test folder.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_044_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The emails are going to the workflow test folder.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_044_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The emails are landing in the workflow test folder.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_044_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "\n\n~arriving into~ is incorrect because 'arrive' takes the prepositions 'in' (for spaces/folders) or 'at' (for points/locations). You cannot arrive 'into' something. Use [arriving in].\n\n~arriving to~ is also not valid for the exact same reason. The verb 'arrive' never pairs with 'to'."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_045",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "El codigo es el mismo, pero estamos apuntando a un lado diferente",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "The code is the same, but we are pointing to a different place.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_045_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The code is the same, but we're pointing somewhere else.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_045_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "It's the same code, but we are pointing to a different environment.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_045_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "\n\n~aiming to a different place~ is not naturally used for servers or code environments. In technical contexts, use [pointing to] a different place, URL, or environment."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_046",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Lo normal seria que mientras esta en produccion, le agregUemos esta feature.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "Normally, while it is in production, we would add this feature.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_046_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The usual thing would be to add this feature while it's in production.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_046_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Ideally, we would add this feature while it is in production.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_046_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The normal way would be to add this feature while it is in production.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_046_sideB_3.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "\n\n~The normal would be~ is a direct translation from Spanish. In English, use an adverb like [Normally] or add a noun like [The normal thing would be]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_047",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Tenemos que reestructurar la infraestructura.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "We have to restructure the infrastructure.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_047_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "We need to rebuild the infrastructure.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_047_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "We have to reorganize the infrastructure.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_047_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_048",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Ha sido un largo tiempo poniendonos al dia en la infraestructura.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "It's taken a long time to get up to speed on the infrastructure.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_048_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "We've spent a long time catching up on the infrastructure.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_048_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "It took a long time to get caught up with the infrastructure.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_048_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "It has been a long time catching up on the infrastructure.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_048_sideB_3.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "\n\n~catching up in the infrastructure~ is not valid because the correct phrasal verb to express bringing yourself up to date on a topic is [catch up on]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_049",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Le pregunte a Jeff acerca de eso, estamos esperando la respuesta de el.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "I asked Jeff about that, we are waiting for his reply.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_049_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I asked Jeff about it, we're waiting for his response.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_049_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I checked with Jeff about that, we're waiting to hear back from him.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_049_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I asked Jeff about that, we are waiting for his answer.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_049_sideB_3.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_050",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Produccion en la base de datos suele cashear las busquedas y ser mas rapida.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "The production database usually caches queries and is faster.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_050_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Production in the database tends to cache the searches and be faster.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_050_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The database in production usually caches the searches, making it faster.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_050_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "\n\n~The database in production use to cache searching~ is not valid because 'use to' implies a past habit that no longer happens. For current routines, you should use [usually caches] or [tends to cache].\n\n~Production in the database use to cache searching~ is incorrect because the subject is reversed. It should be the [database in production]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_051",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Ellas pueden ser deployadas al mismo tiempo, no dependen del uno del otro.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "They can be deployed at the same time, they don't depend on each other.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_051_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "They can be deployed simultaneously, they are not interdependent.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_051_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "They can be rolled out at the same time, they are independent of each other.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_051_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_052",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Necesitaría verlo más a fondo el codigo y sus dependencias para tener una respuesta.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "I would need to look deeper into the code and its dependencies to give you an answer.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_052_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I'd need to take a closer look at the code and its dependencies to have an answer.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_052_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I need to review the code and its dependencies more thoroughly to provide an answer.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_052_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "\n\n~see deeper into~, ~look the code deeper~, and ~see the code deeper~ are not natural. Use [look deeper into the code] or [take a closer look at the code]. The preposition [into] or [at] is required with 'look' in this context, and 'see' is not used for investigating code."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_053",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "No hemos checkeado ese problema aun",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "We haven't checked that issue yet.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_053_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "We haven't looked into that problem yet.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_053_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "We haven't investigated that issue yet.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_053_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_054",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Estoy afuera de la VPN, deja conectarme.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "I'm off the VPN, let me connect.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_054_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I am not on the VPN, give me a second to connect.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_054_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I'm disconnected from the VPN, let me log in.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_054_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "\n\n~out of the VPN~ is a direct translation; in English, we say we are [off] a network or VPN. Also, ~let me connect it~ is incorrect because you do not connect 'the VPN' itself, you connect yourself to it. Use [let me connect] or [let me log in]."
    },
